<span id="freeTextContainer479793483058421907">More enjoyable than the 1st. Mainly because of Fox, the main character and Layla, his love interest. Fox&apos;s character was way more developed than Caleb&apos;s, and more interesting because of the abilities that both him and Layla share. I also enjoyed his courtship with Layla; he was always honest about his attraction to her, but gave her some space to decide. Small-hometown hippie boy hooks up with stylish big-city girl, gotta love it.<br/>In addition, this book marked the 2nd major battle of good vs evil</span>
  <span id="freeText479793483058421907" style="display:none">More enjoyable than the 1st. Mainly because of Fox, the main character and Layla, his love interest. Fox's character was way more developed than Caleb's, and more interesting because of the abilities that both him and Layla share. I also enjoyed his courtship with Layla; he was always honest about his attraction to her, but gave her some space to decide. Small-hometown hippie boy hooks up with stylish big-city girl, gotta love it.<br />In addition, this book marked the 2nd major battle of good vs evil. This time, the connections and bloodlines were better defined than in book #1. The battle was also more intense. It still leaves you at a "to be continued" status, but you are also left with more clarity.</span>
