<span id="freeTextContainer4659279129478818726">Ah, volume two. I think I&apos;m in a bit of a minority of those whom liked the second installment more than the first. <br/><br/>Character-wise I loved it -- I loved watching Fox and Layla fall for each other. It felt so natural and well-timed in comparison to the first. There were lots of bumps and mysteries and trauma along the way, but it all came together to bring them to the people and couple that they are now. <br/><br/>Creep factor was a bit more relaxed (for me). Demon child got in a few really good terrors for</span>
  <span id="freeText4659279129478818726" style="display:none">Ah, volume two. I think I'm in a bit of a minority of those whom liked the second installment more than the first. <br /><br />Character-wise I loved it -- I loved watching Fox and Layla fall for each other. It felt so natural and well-timed in comparison to the first. There were lots of bumps and mysteries and trauma along the way, but it all came together to bring them to the people and couple that they are now. <br /><br />Creep factor was a bit more relaxed (for me). Demon child got in a few really good terrors for the bunch of six that was easy for me to handle as a reader as it was the characters' personal fears rather than more generalized. (If that makes sense?) Horror and violence definitely took an uptick in volume two which is on par with it being March/April and the Seven draws ever closer. Honestly, with how much is already present I shudder to think of what the third and final installment will bring. I don't think I'll be reading that one at night....</span>
